"""
# Launcher Init Spec — SYS-GUI-006 Blocker 2 regression guard

Focused guard for the `[desktop-e2e] launcher:fail registered=0` live-lane
regression. `DesktopShell.init()` invokes `launcher_init()` which registers
four default apps into the module-level registry (`app_name`, `app_path`,
... backed by fixed-size `[T; 32]` globals in
`src/os/services/launcher/launcher.spl`).

In the hosted interpreter this path works and `launcher_get_app_count()`
returns 5. In the baremetal x86_64 desktop lane the same call returns 0,
indicating either module-level array storage is zeroed across the call
boundary, or `DesktopShell.init()`'s method body never executes (bare-method
dispatch picking the wrong `.init()` symbol). Either way, the hosted lane
must keep guarding the launcher-side API contract so any OS-side regression
of `launcher_init()` itself trips a unit failure before shipping to QEMU.

Diagnostic:
  doc/08_tracking/todo/launcher_module_storage_fix_plan_2026-04-14.md
"""

use std.spec
use os.services.launcher.launcher.{launcher_init, launcher_get_app_count}

describe "Launcher init — desktop-ready precondition":
    """Hosted-lane guard for the API contract that `DesktopShell.init()`
    depends on. Any OS-side regression of `launcher_init()` must fail
    here before it can reach the QEMU live lane."""

    it "registers at least one app after launcher_init()":
        """Bare minimum contract — `launcher:fail registered=0` must not
        be reachable from a working `launcher_init()`."""
        launcher_init()
        val count = launcher_get_app_count()
        expect(count > 0).to_be_true()

    it "registers the five default desktop apps":
        """`launcher_init()` seeds Hello World, File Manager, Terminal,
        Browser Demo, and Editor — each required by the SYS-GUI-002 shortcut
        dispatch path."""
        launcher_init()
        val count = launcher_get_app_count()
        expect(count >= 5).to_be_true()
